 constructed from the individual, fragmented\nregions is investigated. Our modeling shows that the introduction of fragmented\ndusty tori significantly alters the resulting net polarization of an AGN.\nComparison of our models to polarization observations of large AGN samples\ngreatly favors geometrically compact clumpy tori over extended ones.\n","versions":[{"version":"v1","created":"Wed, 18 Mar 2015 09:03:23 GMT"}],"update_date":"2015-05-06"}
