 with follow-up\nobservations. The second target, HAT-P-7, is the first F-dwarf star analyzed\nwith the gravity-darkening method. Our analysis points to a nearly pole-on\nconfiguration with $\\psi=101^\\circ\\pm2^\\circ$ or $87^\\circ\\pm2^\\circ$ and the\ngravity-darkening exponent $\\beta$ consistent with $0.25$. Such an\nobservational constraint on $\\beta$ can be useful for testing the theory of\ngravity darkening.\n","versions":[{"version":"v1","created":"Wed, 18 Mar 2015 15:14:10 GMT"},{"version":"v2","created":"Thu, 2 Apr 2015 00:46:47 GMT"}],"update_date":"2015-06-08"}
